Currently there is some inappropriateness in the German translation of JIRA Agile.

{panel}
The German translation of "Commitment" (translated as "Verpflichtung" ) in the Jira Agile Report "Geschwindigkeitsdiagramm" is misleading.
A possible correct translation could be "Geplant".
{panel}

The Bulk Edit screen in JIRA Agile has a text note below the "Change Sprint" field that reads:
{quote}
Sprint field for GreenHopper use only
{quote}

This should be updated to "JIRA Agile".

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-9955].
  {panel}

In an agile board, under "Filter", "Saved Filter", I can left-click to select a saved filter.
However, this dropdown is limited to 20 entries, with no scrolling (see attachment).
I you want to see the 21st entry, you need to know the filter's name, and start typing.

*Rating*: :D Awesome!

{panel:title=What do you like?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#c2ffa2|bgColor=#fff}
No need GreenHopper with all its stuff (fields, entities, etc.) - just simple work in JIRA as you do before and enjoy real burndown chart with no extra effort.
Great job! Thank you guys.
{panel}

{panel:title=What needs to be improved?|borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#faacad|bgColor=#fff}
It would be nice to have 
* a burndown chart for tasks along with efforts burndown;
* a time frame frozen for some recurrent period (like 1 week, 2 weeks, etc. or may be days...) starting from a particular day
{panel}

